CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. A6_A7 reads: "Shriners Leave for L.A. - "California, Here I Come" was the byword and slogan for Pittsburgh area Shriners recently as they headed for the site of their annual convention in Los Angeles, Calif., Aug. 16-21. Among the group leaving Pittsburgh last Thursday night were W. Queen, John Bradford, H. Hill, Wesley Lee, Edward Green, E. Smith, J.W. Foye, Frank White, W. Jackson, J. Goggins, Mrs. M. Roberts and the local Shrine talent winner for 1959, Miss Patricia Prattis. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Sahara Temple Shriners wearing fezzes, including W. Queen, John Bradford, H. Hill, Wesley Lee, Edward Green, E. Smith, J.W. Foye, Frank White, W. Jackson, J. Goggins, Mrs. M. Roberts and Patricia Prattis standing in center, gathered in interior, possibly train station, for trip to annual convention in Los Angeles, CA
